==Trivia==
*In the comics, Gamora possesses different physical characteristics such as green hair and yellow patch-like tattoos over her eyes, and she was eventually entrusted to protect the [[Time Stone|Time Gem]].
*Of all his [[Black Order|adopted children]], [[Thanos]] genuinely loved Gamora, to the extent that not only did he hope that she would inherit his throne one day, but he also genuinely mourned her death after he was forced to [[Sacrifice of Gamora|sacrifice]] her to the [[Soul Stone]] on [[Vormir]].
*Gamora was 275 microbules tall and weighed 852 grets.<ref>[[:File:PHGZQhKAWXqJLJ 1 m.jpg|Gamora's biometrics]]</ref>

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Zoe Saldana]] described Gamora as ''"...a warrior, she's an assassin and she's very lethal but what saves her is the same thing that can doom her. She has a sense of righteousness. She's a very righteous individual."''<ref>[http://www.superherohype.com/news/306737-guardians-of-the-galaxy-from-the-set-of-the-marvel-studios-adaptation ''Guardians of the Galaxy'': From the Set of the Marvel Studios Adaptation]</ref>
*Before Zoe Saldana was cast as Gamora, {{WPS|Olivia Wilde}} and {{WPS|Amanda Seyfried}}<ref>[https://www.instagram.com/darrelljwarner/p/BiyzaycnU7A/ Darrell J. Warner on Instagram - May 15, 2018]</ref><ref name="Amanda Seyfried's rejection to the role of Gamora">[https://www.indiewire.com/2019/08/amanda-seyfried-turned-down-gamora-mcu-1202165221// Amanda Seyfried Apparently Turned Down MCU’s Gamora Because of That Green Makeup]</ref> turned down the role of Gamora, while [[Rosario Dawson]], {{WPS|Gina Carano}}, {{WPS|Rachel Nichols (actress)|Rachel Nichols}}, {{WPS|Kristanna Loken}}, {{WPS|Moon Bloodgood}} and [[Adrianne Palicki]] auditioned before the role.
*[[Chloé Bruce]], [[Lee-Anne Telford]], [[Bethany Levy]] and [[Ana Shepherd]] were stunt doubles for [[Zoe Saldana]] in the role of Gamora.
*[[Abidemi Sobande]], [[Eli Logue]] and [[Anna Elizabeth]] were stand-ins for [[Zoe Saldana]] in the role of Gamora.

